                        <interp inst="t18360509-name-612" type="given" value="CHARLES CROXTON"></interp>CHARLES CROXTON MAY</persName>
                  </hi> I am a silversmith and live in Curtain-road On the 26th of April, about nine o'clock, I was neat Shoreditch church—a policeman asked me if I had lost any thing—I felt and my handkerchief was gone—it was produced to me at the Station-house—it is the same colour as mine—I should not like to swear to it, as there are so many yellow handkerchiefs—I had it safe about half an hour before.</p>
